The paper deals with tracking extended objects, which is a problem in robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a measurement equation and Gaussian state estimator suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of shape models and estimation techniques suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
